        "pairingText": "Merlot, Cabernet Sauvignon, and Pinot Noir are great choices for Roast Beef. Beef and red wine are a classic combination. Generally, leaner cuts of beef go well with light or medium-bodied reds, such as pinot noir or merlot, while fattier cuts can handle a bold red, such as cabernet sauvingnon. The Duckhorn Napa Valley Merlot with a 4.2 out of 5 star rating seems like a good match. It costs about 58 dollars per bottle.",
