      "instructions": "In a bowl, stir to combine buckwheat and egg. In a saucepan over medium heat, add buckwheat and cook for 3 minutes or until grains are dry and separated; stirring frequently. Stir in chicken broth and salt; bring to a boil. Cover and reduce heat to a simmer (low). Simmer for 15 minutes or until the water is absorbed. Remove from heat and add cheeses, stir. In a large saucepan over medium heat, cook bacon until crisp and cooked through, flipping as needed. Remove to a paper towel to drain. To the bacon drippings, add shallots, garlic, and, mushrooms; cook until the mushrooms are golden brown, about 7 minutes. Add kale and sauté until wilted but still bright green; about 2 minutes. Add a pinch of salt and ground black pepper and toss to combine. Serve a large spoonful of buckwheat into each serving bowl. Top with a serving of mushrooms and kale. Crumble bacon and divide the bacon and walnuts over each serving. Serve.",
